'''Nicholas David Brown''' (born 4 December 1962) is a British [[botanist]] and academic. Since 2010, he has been [[Principal (academia)|Principal]] of [[Linacre College, Oxford]].<ref name="Oxford - Dr Nick Brown elected as next Principal of Linacre">{{cite web|title=Dr Nick Brown elected as next Principal of Linacre|url=http://www.ox.ac.uk/media/news_stories/2009/091118.html|work=News|publisher=University of Oxford|accessdate=25 April 2014|date=18 November 2009}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.linacre.ox.ac.uk/about-linacre/college-history|title=College history {{!}} Linacre College|publisher=University of Oxford|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref> He is also a [[Commonwealth Scholarship and Fellowship Plan|Commonwealth Scholarship]] Commissioner.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/people/nick-brown|title=Dr Nick Brown – GOV.UK|website=gov.uk|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref>

==Early life and education==
Brown was born on 4 December 1962 in [[Brockworth, Gloucestershire]], England.<ref name="Who's Who 2016">{{cite web|title=BROWN, Dr Nicholas David|url=http://www.ukwhoswho.com/view/article/oupww/whoswho/U250642|website=Who's Who 2016|publisher=Oxford University Press|accessdate=5 October 2016|date=November 2015}}</ref> He completed the [[IB Diploma Programme|International Baccalaureate]] at UWC Atlantic College in Wales from 1979 to 1981.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/nick-brown-a781717|title=Nick Brown {{!}} LinkedIn|website=www.linkedin.com|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref> He then studied geography at the [[University of Cambridge]] ([[Churchill College, Cambridge|Churchill College]]) between <time>1982 – 1985 and then an MSc in ecology at the [[University of Aberdeen]]</time>.<ref name="Who's Who 2016" /><ref name=":0" /> From 1986 to 1990 he studied for a DPhil in Forest Ecology under the supervision of Timothy Charles Whitmore at the University of Oxford (Linacre College).<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Burley|first=Jeffery|last2=Mills|first2=Roger A|last3=Plumptre|first3=Robert A|last4=Savill|first4=Peter S|last5=Wood|first5=Peter J|last6=Wright|first6=Howard L|title=A History of Forestry at Oxford University|url=http://www.euppublishing.com/doi/pdfplus/10.3366/brs.2009.0007|journal=British Scholar|volume=1|issue=2|pages=236–261|doi=10.3366/brs.2009.0007}}</ref> His thesis was entitled "Dipterocarp regeneration in tropical rain forest gaps of different sizes.".<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Brown|first=N. D.|date=1 January 1990|title=Dipterocarp regeneration in tropical rain forest gaps of different sizes|url=http://solo.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/primo_library/libweb/action/dlDisplay.do?vid=OXVU1&search_scope=LSCOP_OX&docId=oxfaleph010868137&fn=permalink|publisher=Thesis --University of Oxford}}</ref> He has also completed a diploma in Learning and Teaching in Higher Education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Nick_Brown6|title=Nick Brown|website=ResearchGate|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref>

== Career and research ==
Brown was a lecturer at Manchester University from 1989 and then from 1992 to 2010 he was a lecturer in [[forestry]] at the [[University of Oxford]].<ref name="Who's Who 2016" /><ref name="bio - Department of Plant Sciences">{{cite web|url=http://www.plants.ox.ac.uk/plants/staff/NickBrown.aspx|title=Dr ND Brown|date=February 2014|website=People|publisher=Department of Plant Sciences, University of Oxford|accessdate=12 January 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150112211132/http://www.plants.ox.ac.uk/plants/staff/NickBrown.aspx|archivedate=12 January 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dps.plants.ox.ac.uk/ofi/pubs/annrep94.htm|title=Oxford Forestry Institute – Annual Report 1994|publisher=University of Oxford|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.plants.ox.ac.uk/plants/staff/NickBrown.aspx|title=Plant Sciences Staff|date=2015-03-28|access-date=2018-01-16|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150328232041/http://www.plants.ox.ac.uk/plants/staff/NickBrown.aspx|archivedate=28 March 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

In 2010 he took office as the fourth principal of [[Linacre College]], Oxford.<ref name="Oxford - Dr Nick Brown elected as next Principal of Linacre" /><ref name=":1" />

Since 2014 he has been a [[Commonwealth Scholarship and Fellowship Plan|Commonwealth Scholarship]] Commissioner acting as chair of awards policy committee.<ref name=":2" />

Since 2015 he has been the chair of the University of Oxford buildings and estates sub-committee and serves on the planning and resource allocation committee of council.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www1.admin.ox.ac.uk/councilsec/governance/committees/committeemembership/planningandresourceallocationcommitteemembership/buildingsandestatessubcommitteemembership/|title=Buildings and Estates Subcommittee Membership|website=Buildings and Estates Subcommittee Membership|publisher=University of Oxford|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.oxfordfutures.org.uk/uploads/University_of_Oxford_LTP4_response.pdf|title=Connecting Oxfordshire: Local Transport Plan 2015–2031|date=23 March 2015|website=|publisher=Oxford Futures|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref> He also chairs the [[Radcliffe Observatory Quarter]] and the [[Science Area, Oxford|Science Area]] Advisory Boards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/pras/committees/workinggroups/science/|title=ROQ Advisory Board (ROQAB)|website=ROQ Advisory Board (ROQAB)|publisher=University of Oxford|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/pras/committees/workinggroups/science/|title=Science Area Advisory Board (SAAB)|website=Science Area Advisory Board (SAAB)|publisher=University of Oxford|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Brown is married to Dr Roosa Leimu-Brown, a University Lecturer at the [[Department of Plant Sciences, University of Oxford]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.p21c.ox.ac.uk/www.p21c.ox.ac.uk/content/dr-roosa-leimu-brown-0.html|title=Dr Roosa Leimu Brown  {{!}} Plants for the 21st Century Institute|publisher=University of Oxford|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.testforafrica.com|title=TEST for Africa|publisher=testforafrica.com|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref> Brown's hobbies include sailing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.outdoorconservation.eu/team-detail.cfm?teamid=45|title=European Outdoor Conservation Association {{!}} About Us {{!}} Who We Are|website=European Outdoor Conservation Association {{!}} About Us {{!}} Who We Are|access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref>

